                    <span>I cannot put into words the value of this book for either the modern business consultant, general manager, or HR professional.  The book is complete with absolutely wonderful tools to put to good use in your respective organizations.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Tools, Assessments, and Ideas You Can Really Use!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>27</span>
                      /
                      <span>30</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2000-11-20</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The Consultant's Toolkit contains survey tools, assessments, training activities, and step-by-step procedures for organizational development projects that are practical, easy to follow, and easy to customize.  Even though the book is designed for organizational development consultants, in-house training and development personnel will benefit from this book just as much as independent consultants.  There are even surveys, forms, and other tools in this book that can be downloaded so users can edit and print the tools to fit their own specific company or client needs.  Anyone who is responsible for building management coaching skills, leading change, implementing 360 degree or employee surveys, building teams, and enhancing an organization's culture will find ideas they can use immediately.</span>
                  
              
